  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Public Sector Watch</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Identify relevant laws, policies, standards/charters on the issue
Establish who the duty bearers are
Conduct a stakeholder analysis and list boundary partners/potential allies and opponents
Work with allies to craft strategies for influencing the duty bearers
Conduct a baseline to establish current situation on the issue before implementing public policy advocacy (PPA) measures
Implement selected PPA strategies  
Monitor, measure and report on the results arising from implementation of strategies/activities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To obtain more timely service delivery from targeted public sector agencies
To get better customer service support for citizens and encourage the implementation of better service delivery policies in these public sector agencies. 
To encourage and get more  citizen user friendly processes in public sector agencies
To ensure that Public Sector Agencies and Officials facilitate the payment of only approved fees and rates by citizens for services rendered
To identify and highlight any public sector laws, policies or standards which are ineffective and/or are contributing to non-performance in the public sector.
To provide a platform for the concerns of public sector actors to be aired, considered and acted upon.</narrative>
  </description>
